at not so i thought i would add my two coppers.<br>
<br>
I highly recomend the 64meg Extacy by Nvidia, it comes packed with a 200mhz Graphics Processing Unit (GPU) and the GeForce 2 chip set.<br>
<br>
I know i know, there is a GeForce 3 card out there, and hey! if you can afford it, why not, but for the money i would go for the Ge Force 2 since I've seen the GeForce 3s priced arround $300, and the GeForce 2s priced arround $70.<br>
<br>
This is also one of the best times to buy RAM since prices are rock bottom, I bought myself 256megs for $25.  And like most things, i buy the chip, put it in, and then find an even cheaper price.<br>
<br>
a couple things to remember about RAM, I originally had 128megs on one chip, I have 3 slots for ram.  When I bought my new 256chip I put the 256 in the first slot, and moved the 128 over a slot.  Always keep your larger number chip in the first slot.  In some instances a machine will think that slot two has = or lesser ammount of RAM. <br>
Another thing to keep in mind, Don't overload your machine with RAM, I only got 384 and my machine runs great. some people will take a pentium 2 computer running windows 98 or 2000 and buy 3-256meg chips.  This is not only a waste of money but it will mess up the system because the system and opperating system was designed when 256megs was A crap load.<br>
<br>
As Far as processors go, I am currently running a Pentium 2 at 350mhz, and i still bought Luclin.  Yes, Luclin has minimum requirements of 400mhz pentium 2.  But, this must not be too important because I still run Luclin just fine.  sure it takes a while to load the game but when its loaded there is little or no lag.<br>
<br>
also run Dxdiag from your start menu if yer fuzzy about what your system has.  And when upgrading ask yourself how long you think this upgrade will last you.  if yer shooting just to meet a minimum requirement you may be only buying yourself a few months of time since we all know how Verant and Sony like to change the rules at the drop of a hat.<br>
<br>
